Rym: And if you have a problem with that, you can write to your senator and try to get the DMC overturned.

1054
01:10:09,140 --> 01:10:11,851
Rym: But for now, I leave you with...

1055
01:10:14,943 --> 01:10:16,212
Media: I don't want to be an emperor.

1056
01:10:16,635 --> 01:10:17,300
Media: That's not my business.

1057
01:10:19,600 --> 01:10:20,506
Media: ...or conquer anyone.

1058
01:10:20,526 --> 01:10:22,700
Media: I should like to help everyone if possible.

1059
01:10:23,281 --> 01:10:25,460
Media: Jew, Gentile, black man, white.

1060
01:10:26,440 --> 01:10:27,689
Media: We all want to help one another.

1061
01:10:27,971 --> 01:10:29,099
Media: Human beings are like that.

1062
01:10:29,880 --> 01:10:32,080
Media: We want to live by each other's happiness, not by each other's misery.

1063
01:10:33,020 --> 01:10:34,680
Media: We don't want to hate and despise one another.

1064
01:10:35,440 --> 01:10:39,840
Media: In this world, there's room for everyone, and the good earth is rich and can provide for everyone.

1065
01:10:40,460 --> 01:10:44,400
Media: The way of life can be free and beautiful, but we have lost the way.

1066
01:10:45,480 --> 01:10:52,280
Media: Greed has poisoned men's souls, has barricaded the world with hate, has goose-stepped us into misery and bloodshed.

1067
01:10:53,181 --> 01:10:55,799
Media: We have developed speed, but we have shut ourselves in.

1068
01:10:56,600 --> 01:10:58,679
Media: Machinery that gives abundance has left us in want.

1069
01:10:59,420 --> 01:11:02,640
Media: Our knowledge has made us cynical, our cleverness hard and unkind.

1070
01:11:03,321 --> 01:11:05,399
Media: We think too much and feel too little.

1071
01:11:06,120 --> 01:11:08,240
Media: More than machinery, we need humanity.

1072
01:11:08,761 --> 01:11:11,540
Media: More than cleverness, we need kindness and gentleness.

1073
01:11:12,263 --> 01:11:15,520
Media: Without these qualities, life will be violent and all will be lost.

1074
01:11:16,400 --> 01:11:18,680
Media: The aeroplane and the radio have brought us closer together.

1075
01:11:19,060 --> 01:11:24,859
Media: The very nature of these inventions cries out for the goodness in men, cries out for universal brotherhood, for the unity of us all.

1076
01:11:25,560 --> 01:11:35,720
Media: Even now, my voice is reaching millions throughout the world, millions of despairing men, women and little children, victims of a system that makes men torture and imprison innocent people.

1077
01:11:36,641 --> 01:11:39,340
Media: To those who can hear me, I say, do not despair.

1078
01:11:39,964 --> 01:11:46,100
Media: The misery that is now upon us is but the passing of greed, the bitterness of men who fear the way of human progress.

1079
01:11:46,781 --> 01:11:53,120
Media: The hate of men will pass and dictators die, and the power they took from the people will return to the people.

1080
01:11:53,521 --> 01:11:56,439
Media: And so long as men die, liberty will never perish.

1081
01:11:58,541 --> 01:12:00,539
Rym: Soldiers, don't give yourselves to brutes.

1082
01:12:01,200 --> 01:12:10,600
Rym: Men who despise you, enslave you, who regiment your lives, tell you what to do, what to think and what to feel, who drill you, diet you, treat you like cattle, use you as cannon fodder.

1083
01:12:11,161 --> 01:12:16,659
Media: Don't give yourselves to these unnatural men, machine men, with machine minds and machine hearts.

1084
01:12:17,261 --> 01:12:20,339
Media: You are not machines, you are not cattle, you are men.

1085
01:12:21,021 --> 01:12:22,759
Media: You have the love of humanity in your hearts.

1086
01:12:23,180 --> 01:12:26,960
Media: You don't hate, only the unloved hate, the unloved and the unnatural.

1087
01:12:27,500 --> 01:12:30,420
Rym: Soldiers, don't fight for slavery, fight for liberty.

1088
01:12:30,860 --> 01:12:32,073
Media: In the 17th chapter of St.

1089
01:12:32,114 --> 01:12:42,780
Media: Luke it is written, the kingdom of God is within man, not one man nor a group of men, but in all men, in you, you the people have the power, the power to create machines, the power to create happiness.

1090
01:12:43,160 --> 01:12:48,460
Media: You the people have the power to make this life free and beautiful, to make this life a wonderful adventure.

1091
01:12:48,921 --> 01:13:01,140
Scott: Then in the name of democracy, let us use that power, let us all unite, let us fight for a new world, a decent world that will give men a chance to work, that will give youth a future and old age a security.

1092
01:13:01,600 --> 01:13:07,799
Media: By the promise of these things, brutes have risen to power, but they lie, they do not fulfill that promise, they never will.

1093
01:13:08,380 --> 01:13:11,460
Media: Dictators free themselves, but they enslave the people.

1094
01:13:12,021 --> 01:13:22,100
Media: Now let us fight to fulfill that promise, let us fight to free the world, to do away with national barriers, to do away with greed, with hate and intolerance.

1095
01:13:22,881 --> 01:13:28,820
Rym: Let us fight for a world of reason, a world where science and progress will lead to all men's happiness.

1096
01:13:29,780 --> 01:13:33,159
Scott: Soldiers, in the name of democracy, let us all unite!

